dcterms:description: The Dow Jones Industrial Index (DJI) is a stock market index that represents 30 large publicly owned companies trading on the New York Stock Exchange (NYSE) and the NASDAQ. It is used as a benchmark for the performance of the U.S. stock market.
dcterms:title: Dow Jones Industrial Index (DJI)

dcterms:description: The SSE50 is an index that represents the top 50 companies listed on the Shanghai Stock Exchange in China. It is used to gauge the performance of the Chinese stock market.
dcterms:title: SSE50

dcterms:description: SENSEX is a stock market index that represents 30 of the largest and most actively traded stocks on the Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) in India. It serves as a benchmark for the Indian stock market.
dcterms:title: SENSEX

dcterms:description: FTSE 100 is a stock market index that represents the 100 largest companies listed on the London Stock Exchange by market capitalization. It is used as a key indicator of the performance of the UK stock market.
dcterms:title: FTSE 100

dcterms:description: HIST is a high-frequency trading simulator developed by Microsoft Research Asia, designed to provide a realistic environment for developing and testing high-frequency trading algorithms.
